{{notability|books|date=December 2010}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Dead Space: Martyr | image = Dead Space Martyr cover.jpg | image_size = 200px | orig title = | translator = | author = [[Brian Evenson|B.K. Evenson]] | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | genre = [[Science fiction]], [[Horror fiction|Horror]] | publisher = [[Tor Books]] | release_date = July 2010 | media_type = Print (paperback) | pages = 416 p. (paperback edition) | isbn = 0-7653-2503-9 | isbn_note = (paperback edition) | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Dead Space: Martyr''''' is a 2010 [[science fiction]] novel by [[Brian Evenson|B.K. Evenson]].<ref name="ugosource">http://www.ugo.com/games/award-winning-horror-writer-to-pen-dead-space-prequel {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100418063033/http://www.ugo.com/games/award-winning-horror-writer-to-pen-dead-space-prequel |date=April 18, 2010 }}</ref>
==Plot== The novel delves into the origins of Church of Unitology, Michael Altman, Necromorphs and the mysterious Black Marker in the [[Dead Space (series)|''Dead Space'']] universe.<ref name="ugosource"/> The story revolves around geophysicist Michael Altman as he investigates the source of a mysterious signal and uncovers a strange alien artifact. The narrative then goes on to focus on how Altman's actions led to his own unwilling "martyrdom," the origin of the Red Marker, and the subsequent birth of the Church of Unitology.
